result.execSummary:
The defendant Wade Brandon Bassatt was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Wade Brandon Bassatt is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Wade Brandon Bassatt was found guilty of Burglary-Building or Dwelling, a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Wade Brandon Bassatt in court with attorney Roger M. Hillestad.  Defendant Wade Brandon Bassatt in custody.  Sean Froelich appeared by phone means for the State of Wisconsin. Counsel informs of agreement, plea to 1 count of burglary, counsel free to argue sentencing. Court advises defendant of count 1/max penalties.  Defendant enters plea of guilty.  PLQ/WOR form filed with the court and reviewed with defendant. Defendant a citizen of the US; agrees the facts support the charge. Court finds defendant's waiver of his constitutional rights and plea done knowingly & voluntarily, accepts plea and finds defendant guilty.  State moves to dismiss counts 2 & 3.  Counts 2 & 3 dismissed.  No PSI requested by either side.  PSI was done recently in his Pierce County case and was sentenced there to 6 yrs. WI State Prison; 2 1/2 yrs. IC; 3 1/2 yrs. ES for felon possession of firearm.  State notes victims rights complied with, no VIS; requests concurrent sentence to Pierce County Case No. 2014CF127; IC 3 1/2 yrs; 2 1/2 yrs ES.  Atty Hillestad recommends 2 yrs IC; 5 yrs ES. Court sentences defendant to 6 yrs. WI State Prison; 2 1/2 yrs IC; 3 1/2 yrs ES; credit for 172 days served; concurrent with Pierce Co. 2014CF127; find eligible for CIP & ERP; conditions of ES:  pay costs; comply with any assessment or counseling set up by DOC; advised of felony prohibitions, appeal rights; Defendant consents to Mr. Froelich's appearance by phone today.
